Massive dead empty space below the social icons before the next section starts. Fix: Either increase hero height to fill the viewport properly, or add a scroll indicator arrow to intentionally anchor the bottom.

"I'm Sugumaran" apostrophe makes the heading optically off-center. Fix: Apply optical margin alignment, or rephrase to avoid the apostrophe shift entirely.

Hero content block is too narrow — huge blank space left and right. Fix: Let the surrounding hero area fill the viewport width with a background treatment while keeping the content at max-width 700–800px.

"Full Stack Developer" subtitle sits too close to the name. Fix: Increase margin-top on the subtitle to at least 8–12px.

Gap between subtitle and tagline paragraph is too large and inconsistent. Fix: Standardize spacing to around 24px between each element — name, subtitle, paragraph, buttons, icons.

Tagline paragraph line break wraps awkwardly — uneven two-line split. Fix: Set max-width 520px on the paragraph so lines break naturally and evenly.

"Download CV" and "Get In Touch" buttons have mismatched heights. Fix: Ensure both share the same padding and height values.

Two CTA buttons look near identical in visual weight — no primary vs secondary distinction. Fix: Make Download CV a solid filled button and Get In Touch a ghost outline button to clearly separate their hierarchy.

Button sizes feel small relative to the surrounding empty space. Fix: Increase button padding to at least 12px 28px, minimum height 44px.

Three social icons are unevenly spaced — LinkedIn and Mail sit closer together than GitHub and LinkedIn. Fix: Use consistent gap of 20px between all three icons in a flex container.

Social icons have no labels. Fix: Add tooltip labels on hover, or add small text labels below each icon.

Social icons feel disconnected from the buttons above. Fix: Add consistent margin-top of 32px to create intentional visual separation as a deliberate group.

Nothing anchors the bottom of the hero — abruptly cuts into the next section. Fix: Add a subtle scroll indicator animated chevron or arrow, or a soft gradient fade at the bottom.

"Sugumaran S" in navbar and "I'm Sugumaran" in hero repeat immediately — visual stutter. Fix: Either remove the name from the navbar logo and use initials or an icon, or rephrase the hero headline to avoid the direct repeat.

