**GLOBAL LAYOUT**

Every single section uses the exact same centered title, subtitle, content structure — zero layout variation across the entire page. Fix: Alternate section layouts — some left-aligned, some full-width, some with a two-column split — to create rhythm and visual flow.

Section transitions are abrupt with no spacing rhythm. Fix: Set a consistent global section padding of 80–100px top and bottom and apply it without exception across every section.

Content width is inconsistent across sections — some feel wider than others. Fix: Set a single max-width 1100px container class and wrap every section's content in it.

No visual landmark or anchor that makes any single section memorable. Fix: Give at least one section a distinct layout treatment — a full-bleed background, an offset grid, or a bold typographic moment.

Page feels like stacked identical blocks with no personality or flow connecting them. Fix: Use spacing variation, alignment shifts, and at least one visually distinct section to break the monotony and create a sense of intentional design.




